p://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Dairy industry brainwashing.</span><hr size=1> This is a little off topic, but goes along with the cow's milk thing.  My ds (15 months) doesn't drink a milk bottle.  I still give him formula.  My dh has crohn's disease and he read an article that showed a possible connection. There is a bacteria that isn't killed in pasturization that was always considered harmless, but now they(the infamous they) say that there may be a connection with crohn's disease.  It would only take an extra 20 seconds to kill this bacteria, but the dairy community refuses.  To do go the extra 20 seconds would be admitting that they were selling something unsafe.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  There isn't anyone else in his family that has crohn's so the genetic factor isn't really there for him.  When he was younger and still lived at home they would go through a gallon of milk a day because of him mostly.  So, now he will not take that chance with his ds.  I would still be nursing ds, but he decided that he was done at about 9 1/2 months.  So I put him on formula.  He doesn't even have a bottle all that often and he drinks water most of the time.  While I am on the subject, does anyone know of a good vitamin for infants?  I should be supplementing his diet.  <br>
<br>
Anyway, that is my two cents.<br>
